M ucel-wudu is, however, the true equivalent for Magna Silva (Mickle Wood). The name occurs twice, and is written on one occasion Mucel-Pudu, on the other still more corruptly, Mucel-Purlu. From the same confusion between the Anglo- Saxon P and W, Coitmawr is on both occasions written Coitmapur.
